window.bookSummaryJSON = "The Victorian-era writers featured in this collection are known for their power of invention and command of horror and the supernatural. <p>Included are \"A Watcher by the Dead\" by Ambrose Bierce; \"The Body Snatchers\" by Robert Louis Stevenson; \"The Adventure of the German Student\" by Washington Irving; \"Dickon the Devil\" by J. Sheridan Le Fanu; \"The Fall of the House of Usher\" by Edgar Allan Poe; and \"The Open Watcher\" by Saki.</p>"; 
